1969
02:12:31,479 --> 02:12:33,160
<i>How would you describe the
relationship overall?</i>

1970
02:12:33,239 --> 02:12:35,920
<i>Did you talk on the phone a lot?
Were there a lot of visits?</i>

1971
02:12:36,640 --> 02:12:40,160
I would say we talked on the phone a
couple of times a month, at least.

1972
02:12:40,239 --> 02:12:43,680
Sometimes more than that. I would
call her, she would call me.

1973
02:12:44,439 --> 02:12:47,560
<i>And what were the nature
of the conversations?</i>

1974
02:12:47,640 --> 02:12:50,560
Oh, family stuff, mostly.
Her family, my kids.

1975
02:12:50,640 --> 02:12:52,960
She'd give you advice about your family?
That kind of thing?

1976
02:12:53,039 --> 02:12:55,480
Oh, I would say so, yes.

1977
02:12:56,039 --> 02:12:57,160
Do you have any phone records?

1978
02:12:57,279 --> 02:13:00,000
I have all my phone bills,
if that's what you mean.

1979
02:13:00,319 --> 02:13:02,160
I didn't record the
actual conversations.

1980
02:13:02,239 --> 02:13:03,320
No, no.

1981
02:13:03,399 --> 02:13:06,240
You'll see we talked on the
phone quite frequently.

1982
02:13:06,319 --> 02:13:10,160
- Okay, terrific. I see you came prepared.
- Well, I wanted to bring everything.

1983
02:13:10,479 --> 02:13:12,920
Now, when they take your deposition,

1984
02:13:13,000 --> 02:13:14,760
you're gonna say the same
thing you just told me.

1985
02:13:14,880 --> 02:13:16,120
Just talk about the relationship.

1986
02:13:16,399 --> 02:13:17,400
Uh-huh.

1987
02:13:17,640 --> 02:13:20,200
- Kind of advice she used to give.
- Okay.

1988
02:13:23,119 --> 02:13:26,200
Now, Emily, where did
you find this lawyer?

1989
02:13:28,000 --> 02:13:30,360
He was recommended by my friend.

1990
02:13:31,079 --> 02:13:35,240
I'm asking because my husband
knows a real good New York lawyer

1991
02:13:35,680 --> 02:13:38,840
and I'm not entirely comfortable
with someone no one's ever heard of.

1992
02:13:39,039 --> 02:13:42,120
My friend's heard of him.
He says he's very good.

1993
02:13:42,199 --> 02:13:43,400
Well, I'm sure he is.

1994
02:13:43,479 --> 02:13:46,880
But I have a responsibility
in this situation

1995
02:13:46,960 --> 02:13:50,800
and I would feel a whole lot more
comfortable with someone who didn't just

1996
02:13:50,880 --> 02:13:52,480
drop in out of the clear blue sky.

1997
02:13:52,560 --> 02:13:55,040
He didn't drop in out
of the clear blue sky.

1998
02:13:55,159 --> 02:13:59,640
But, Abigail, even if we switched
lawyers, we would still have to pay him.

1999
02:13:59,760 --> 02:14:02,840
But it all comes out of the
settlement, so it's really up to you.

2000
02:14:02,920 --> 02:14:04,760
No, if you all think he's good...

2001
02:14:04,960 --> 02:14:06,560
I don't know whether he is or not.

2002
02:14:06,640 --> 02:14:09,320
- My friend thinks he is.
- All right.

2003
02:14:11,000 --> 02:14:13,560
Now, Lisa, what's your
involvement in all this?

2004
02:14:13,640 --> 02:14:15,240
What's your angle?

2005
02:14:17,560 --> 02:14:19,120
I was just there.

2006
02:14:32,960 --> 02:14:35,800
Oh, my God, is that you?

2007
02:14:37,720 --> 02:14:39,000
That's me.

2008
02:14:39,479 --> 02:14:41,760
And that's you and Monica, obviously.

2009
02:14:42,720 --> 02:14:43,960
Mmm-hmm.

2010
02:14:46,159 --> 02:14:47,880
Is that her daughter?

2011
02:14:49,000 --> 02:14:50,040
Mmm-hmm.

2012
02:14:51,039 --> 02:14:52,160
God.

2013
02:14:52,279 --> 02:14:54,080
So, how old was she when she died?

2014
02:14:55,800 --> 02:14:56,840
Twelve.

2015
02:14:58,079 --> 02:14:59,800
God, I can't even imagine.

2016
02:15:00,640 --> 02:15:01,720
Neither could we.

2017
02:15:08,359 --> 02:15:11,800
Do you know Monica asked about
her when she was dying?

2018
02:15:14,239 --> 02:15:15,600
No, I didn't.

2019
02:15:15,760 --> 02:15:18,160
Yeah, I think she was confused, like,

2020
02:15:18,239 --> 02:15:20,480
I think she thought I was
her daughter for a minute.

2021
02:15:20,720 --> 02:15:24,040
And then she was asking me to call her,
like, to tell her what happened, you know?

2022
02:15:24,119 --> 02:15:26,200
Like she didn't remember she was dead.

2023
02:15:27,640 --> 02:15:31,640
But, then it got confusing, because
I said, "sure, what's her name?"

2024
02:15:32,039 --> 02:15:35,240
And she said her name was Lisa.
And I said, "no, that's my name. "

2025
02:15:35,319 --> 02:15:37,080
Because it took me a minute.

2026
02:15:37,640 --> 02:15:40,240
I didn't realize we had the same name.

2027
02:15:45,199 --> 02:15:47,680
But then, when I found out
her daughter was dead,

2028
02:15:47,760 --> 02:15:49,320
ever since then

2029
02:15:49,399 --> 02:15:54,560
I've had this really strange feeling that,
some way, for those last five minutes,

2030
02:15:55,399 --> 02:15:57,320
I kind of was her daughter.

2031
02:15:57,920 --> 02:16:01,360
You know, like in some weird way,
this obviously amazing woman

2032
02:16:01,439 --> 02:16:05,200
got to be with her daughter again for
a few minutes, right before she died.

2033
02:16:05,279 --> 02:16:06,440
I see.

2034
02:16:07,199 --> 02:16:09,200
And is she still inhabiting your body?

2035
02:16:09,279 --> 02:16:12,200
Or did she go right back to the
spirit world after it was over?

2036
02:16:12,279 --> 02:16:14,640
I didn't mean she was
literally inhabiting my body.

2037
02:16:14,720 --> 02:16:15,960
I don't believe in all
that stuff at all.

2038
02:16:16,119 --> 02:16:18,400
I don't give a fuck
what you believe in.

2039
02:16:18,479 --> 02:16:20,640
Oh, my God! Why are you so mad at me?

2040
02:16:20,720 --> 02:16:22,480
Because this is not an opera!

2041
02:16:22,560 --> 02:16:24,840
- What?
- I said this is not an opera!

2042
02:16:24,920 --> 02:16:26,640
You think I think this is an opera?

2043
02:16:26,720 --> 02:16:28,560
- Yes!
- You think I think this is dramatic?

2044
02:16:28,640 --> 02:16:29,840
I think you're very young.

2045
02:16:29,920 --> 02:16:31,200
What does that have
to do with anything?

2046
02:16:31,279 --> 02:16:34,040
If anything, I think it means I
care more than someone who's older,

2047
02:16:34,120 --> 02:16:36,200
because this kind of thing has
never happened to me before!

2048
02:16:36,280 --> 02:16:40,480
No, it means you care more easily.
There's a big difference.

2049
02:16:40,879 --> 02:16:42,800
Only it's not you that
it's happening to.

2050
02:16:42,920 --> 02:16:45,880
Yes, it is! I know I'm not the
one who was run over by a bus...

2051
02:16:45,959 --> 02:16:47,320
That's right, you weren't.

2052
02:16:47,399 --> 02:16:49,280
And you're not the one
who died of leukemia,

2053
02:16:49,360 --> 02:16:52,160
and you're not the one who just
died in an earthquake in Algeria!

2054
02:16:52,239 --> 02:16:54,800
But you will be. Do you understand me?
You will be.

2055
02:16:54,959 --> 02:16:57,040
And it's not dramatic,
and it's not an opera.

2056
02:16:57,120 --> 02:16:58,520
I'm well aware of that!

2057
02:16:58,600 --> 02:17:02,400
This first-blush, phony deepness
of yours is worth nothing.

2058
02:17:02,479 --> 02:17:03,480
- Oh, wow.
- Do you understand?

2059
02:17:03,600 --> 02:17:05,000
It's not worth anything!

2060
02:17:05,120 --> 02:17:07,240
Because it'll all be troweled
over in a month or two.

2061
02:17:07,319 --> 02:17:08,320
And when you get older

2062
02:17:08,399 --> 02:17:11,480
and you don't have a big reaction
every time a dog is run over,

2063
02:17:11,559 --> 02:17:13,680
then we'll find out what
kind of a person you are!

2064
02:17:13,760 --> 02:17:17,120
I'm sorry, but I didn't start this
conversation and I don't play these games.

2065
02:17:17,200 --> 02:17:20,080
- I'm not playing games!
- And don't look so outraged!

2066
02:17:20,159 --> 02:17:22,240
You have every right to
falsify your own life,

2067
02:17:22,319 --> 02:17:24,600
but you have no right to
falsify anybody else's.

2068
02:17:24,680 --> 02:17:27,120
It's what makes people into Nazis!

2069
02:17:27,200 --> 02:17:28,800
And I'm sorry, but it's
a little suspicious

2070
02:17:28,879 --> 02:17:31,680
you're making such a big fuss about
this when you didn't even know her

2071
02:17:31,760 --> 02:17:33,240
and you're having troubles
with your own mother.

2072
02:17:33,319 --> 02:17:34,360
Oh, my God!

2073
02:17:34,440 --> 02:17:38,920
But this is my life that we're talking
about, much more than it is yours,

2074
02:17:39,000 --> 02:17:44,920
because it's my real friend who got
killed, who I'm never going to see again,

2075
02:17:45,559 --> 02:17:50,120
really, who I've known since
I was 19 years old myself.

2076
02:17:50,879 --> 02:17:54,080
And I don't want that sucked into
some adolescent self-dramatization!

2077
02:17:54,159 --> 02:17:58,400
I'm not fucking dramatizing anything!
I was there and you weren't,

2078
02:17:58,479 --> 02:18:00,840
and if I happen to express myself
a little hyperbolically, Emily,

2079
02:18:00,920 --> 02:18:02,400
that's just the way I talk!

2080
02:18:02,479 --> 02:18:06,000
I can't help it if my mother's an actress!
Why are you being so fucking strident?

2081
02:18:07,440 --> 02:18:08,640
- "Strident"?
- Yeah.

2082
02:18:08,719 --> 02:18:09,800
Okay.

2083
02:18:10,719 --> 02:18:11,760
You should leave.

2084
02:18:11,840 --> 02:18:13,040
Why? Because I called you strident?

2085
02:18:13,479 --> 02:18:15,640
Yeah. Strident. You should leave.

2086
02:18:15,719 --> 02:18:17,080
Okay, I will.

2087
02:18:17,159 --> 02:18:18,680
- Now!
- Okay, let me get my bag!

2088
02:18:19,639 --> 02:18:21,800
Does this mean we're
dropping the whole inquiry?

2089
02:18:21,879 --> 02:18:24,360
It means you're leaving. I
don't know what else it means.

2090
02:18:24,440 --> 02:18:26,120
All I meant by saying
that you were strident

2091
02:18:26,200 --> 02:18:27,720
is that you were being emphatic!

2092
02:18:27,799 --> 02:18:29,200
I obviously misused the word.

2093
02:18:29,280 --> 02:18:31,840
- Look it up when you get home.
- Jesus Christ. You're amazing.

2094
02:18:31,920 --> 02:18:34,560
- Yes. I'm amazing.
- Why are you doing this?

2095
02:18:34,639 --> 02:18:38,040
Lisa, I'm not doing anything.
I'm a human being.

2096
02:18:38,120 --> 02:18:40,000
Monica was a human being.

2097
02:18:40,079 --> 02:18:41,760
So was her daughter and
so is your mother.

2098
02:18:41,840 --> 02:18:45,440
We are not supporting characters in
the fascinating story of your life.

2099
02:18:45,520 --> 02:18:47,280
I never said or thought you were,

2100
02:18:47,360 --> 02:18:50,920
and I really didn't mean to call you 
strident. I totally misused the word.

2101
02:18:51,000 --> 02:18:53,520
I feel so bad about
what happened,

2102
02:18:53,600 --> 02:18:56,320
and I'm trying so hard to
do something about it.

2103
02:18:56,399 --> 02:18:58,560
And I don't understand why,
if I say something wrong,

2104
02:18:58,639 --> 02:19:00,800
you can't just give me a break.

2105
02:19:00,879 --> 02:19:03,080
But I'm not trying to
dramatize anything, Emily.

2106
02:19:03,159 --> 02:19:06,440
I really do know about that trend, and I
really don't think I've been doing that.

2107
02:19:11,079 --> 02:19:12,560
Thanks for letting me come over.

2108
02:19:13,079 --> 02:19:14,440
I know you don't want me here.

2109
02:19:14,520 --> 02:19:16,840
<i>No, it's not that.</i>

2110
02:19:16,920 --> 02:19:18,840
But I didn't have
anyone else to talk to.

2111
02:19:19,440 --> 02:19:22,360
You've always been very
sympathetic to my craziness,

2112
02:19:22,440 --> 02:19:25,800
and I may not show it all the time,
but I actually really appreciate it.

2113
02:19:26,000 --> 02:19:27,360
It's no problem.

2114
02:19:31,360 --> 02:19:32,520
So...

2115
02:19:33,159 --> 02:19:34,520
What's been going on?

2116
02:19:35,840 --> 02:19:37,040
I just need to talk to somebody

2117
02:19:37,120 --> 02:19:40,320
who doesn't completely
misunderstand who I am.

2118
02:19:40,600 --> 02:19:42,200
Or not even who I am,

2119
02:19:42,280 --> 02:19:45,120
but what's going on inside
me, or all around me.

2120
